          "CAPA effectiveness verification plan: (1) VISION SYSTEM INTERLOCK (Verify within 30 days): For each upgraded line, conduct a CHALLENGE TEST: attempt to start the line with vision in bypass mode — verify the interlock prevents it. Document the test with video. Repeat quarterly. Success criteria: 100% of attempts blocked, zero production runs with vision in bypass in the past 30 days, (2) LINE CLEARANCE SOP (Verify within 60 days): Conduct UNANNOUNCED audits of line clearance during changeovers across all 12 lines. Observer evaluates compliance with the equipment-specific checklist, photographic documentation, and feeder inspection. Success criteria: ≥95% compliance rate across 20 observed changeovers. Any non-compliance triggers immediate re-training, (3) LABEL RECONCILIATION (Verify within 60 days): Review label reconciliation records for ALL batches packaged since the new zero-tolerance SOP went effective. Success criteria: zero batches released with unresolved reconciliation discrepancies. Track: number of production stops triggered by reconciliation discrepancies (expected to increase initially — this is GOOD, it means the system is catching issues), (4) PRODUCT SCHEDULING (Verify within 90 days): Review 3 months of production schedules for compliance with LASA scheduling restrictions. Verify that no NTI-NTI back-to-back runs occurred without the prescribed enhanced changeover protocol. Success criteria: 100% compliance with scheduling restrictions, (5) POST-MAINTENANCE VERIFICATION (Verify within 90 days): Audit maintenance records for all vision system, metal detector, and checkweigher maintenance events. Verify QA sign-off and functional test documentation for every event. Success criteria: 100% compliance — zero safety-critical systems returned to production without QA verification, (6) TRAINING EFFECTIVENESS (Verify within 90 days): 100% of affected personnel trained on revised SOPs with documented competency assessment. Random knowledge checks: pull 10% of trained employees for spot-check interviews on line clearance procedure, LASA awareness, and escalation criteria. Success criteria: ≥90% of spot-checked employees demonstrate understanding, (7) CULTURE METRICS (Verify within 180 days): Baseline quality culture survey completed. Near-miss reporting rate tracked. Target: ≥5 near-miss reports per line per month by Month 6. First leadership gemba walk completed and documented, (8) RECALL PROCESS (Verify within 120 days): Conduct a MOCK RECALL drill: select a random batch, execute the recall process, measure time to contact all distribution points. Success criteria: 100% of distribution points contacted within 24 hours, (9) CAPA CLOSURE CRITERIA — CAPA-2026-0201 may be closed ONLY when: (a) all 12 lines have validated vision system interlocks, (b) 60-day line clearance audit shows ≥95% compliance, (c) zero reconciliation discrepancy releases for 90 days, (d) 100% training completion with competency, (e) mock recall meets 24-hour target. Estimated closure: 6 months from CAPA opening, (10) ONGOING MONITORING — After CAPA closure, maintain: quarterly interlock challenge tests, monthly line clearance audits (reduced frequency from unannounced), annual mock recall, and annual quality culture survey. Include packaging safety metrics as a standing agenda item in Monthly Quality Review and Annual Management Review. Present to CDSCO inspector as evidence of a mature, self-correcting quality system.",
